<P>
SUPERPOWERS AIM FOR SAFE SEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN FRANCISCO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Superpower relations are now so close that America is going to help make sex 
safe in the Soviet Union. 
</P>
<P>
Mayer Laboratories Inc. and Soviet-American Business Opportunites Inc. said 
Monday they have signed an agreement with the Ukrainian Ministry of Health to 
make, market and distribute condoms in the Soviet Union. 
</P>
<P>
They expect to make 225 million condoms a year at a factory in Kiev, doubling 
the number now available annually in the Soviet Union. 
