<HEADLINE>
<P>
OXNARD MAN ACCIDENTALLY RUNS OVER, KILLS BABY DAUGHTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GARY GORMAN, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Oxnard man accidentally ran over and killed his 18-month-old daughter Monday 
morning in the alley behind their home, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Felipe Serrato, 22, had backed his 1976 Oldsmobile Cutlass into the alley 
behind the 1200 block of West Fir Avenue, police traffic investigator Jeff 
Shelton said. 
</P>
<P>
As Serrato pulled forward, Adeline Serrato ran from the fenced yard and was 
struck by the car. 
</P>
<P>
"He didn't see her," Shelton said. "It happened so fast." 
</P>
<P>
Adeline was pronounced dead at St. John's Regional Medical Center in Oxnard at 
11:35 a.m., about 45 minutes after the accident. 
</P>
<P>
An autopsy was pending, but Deputy Coroner Dale Zentzis said the cause of death 
appeared to be head injuries. 
</P>
<P>
No charges were filed, Shelton said. "It wasn't his fault," he said. 
</P>
<P>
The baby's mother did not see the accident but was home when it occurred, 
Shelton said, adding that the mother is seven months pregnant. 
</P>
<P>
"The whole family has been destroyed," Serrato's brother, Melchor Serrato, said 
in a telephone interview. 
</P>
<P>
Speaking in Spanish as the parents and other family members sobbed in the 
background, he said that Felipe Serrato is a farm worker and that the couple 
have no other children. 
</P>
<P>
"It's a sad one," Zentzis said. "The poor dad . . . that would be awful." 
</P>
</TEXT>
