<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three men were arrested Monday on suspicion of false imprisonment after they 
allegedly held five Mexicans at knifepoint. 
</P>
<P>
According to police, the three men were smuggling the illegal immigrants to Los 
Angeles, but stopped at a load house in San Diego, where they demanded more 
money. 
</P>
<P>
Load houses are used by smugglers to hold undocumented immigrants and transfer 
them to vehicles used to transport them to their destination. 
</P>
<P>
The five men were held at the house for about five hours until one escaped 
through a second-story window and called San Diego police at 9 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
Sergio Cruz Pena, 18; Jesus Lopez Rivera, 23, and Alberto Sanchez-Ortega are 
being held in County Jail. The three are also undocumented immigrants. 
</P>
<P>
The five immigrants were released to Border Patrol officers to be deported back 
to Mexico. 
</P>
</TEXT>
