<HEADLINE>
<P>
AGENT SAYS NO DECISION YET BY RILEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LARRY STEWART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ed Hookstratten, Pat Riley's agent, Monday night denied broadcast reports that 
the Laker coach has decided not to return to the team next season. 
</P>
<P>
"Negotiations with NBC have commenced, but no decision as to Riley's future 
with the Lakers has been made," Hookstratten said. 
</P>
<P>
Riley had dinner with Dick Ebersol, president of NBC Sports, and Terry O'Neil, 
executive producer, Wednesday in New York to discuss joining the network as an 
NBA commentator. 
</P>
<P>
KCBS' Keith Olbermann, quoting unnamed sources, reported chances are "slim at 
best" that Riley will be back. 
</P>
<P>
Riley could not be reached for comment. LARRY STEWART 
</P>
</TEXT>
