<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: DAMON GROUP REPORTS LOSS IN 2ND QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Damon Group Inc. in Sherman Oaks said it lost $1.89 million in its fiscal 
second quarter that ended March 31, compared with a loss of $371,000 a year 
earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Damon Group, which recently changed its name from American Magnetics Corp., 
also has changed its focus to medical testing labs from manufacturing 
electronic bank card and credit card readers. 
</P>
<P>
Last year, the company invested in a chain of medical labs and recently it 
announced the $12-million sale of its magnetic card business, which is to be 
completed June 15. 
</P>
<P>
As a result of the lab chain's contribution, Damon Group's sales soared to 
$51.7 million in the second quarter from $322,000 for the same period a year 
earlier. 
</P>
<P>
For the six months ended March 31, Damon lost $2.7 million, compared to a 
$531,000 loss a year earlier. Its six-month sales climbed to $101.9 million 
from $640,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
