<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: PERFECTDATA REPORTS HUGE JUMP IN PROFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PerfectData Corp., a Simi Valley maker of maintenance supplies for computer 
equipment, said its fiscal fourth-quarter profit jumped to $125,000 from 
$34,000 a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
The earnings gain in the quarter that ended March 31 came on an increase in 
sales to $1.39 million from $1 million, and reflected product introductions and 
cost controls, the company said. 
</P>
<P>
For its full fiscal year, PerfectData earned $132,000, compared with $10,000 
the previous year, and its annual sales climbed to $4.05 million from $3.6 
million. 
</P>
