<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Mark I. Pinsky and Steve Emmons 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TURNOUT: The county is "hoping" for a 50% turnout of registered voters today in 
a non-presidential primary. . . . Not bad? Actually, that would amount to only 
31% of county residents old enough to vote. . . . By contrast, turnout in 
Nicaragua's election last February was about 90%. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
O.C. TURNOUT 
</P>
<P>
1988 General Election 
</P>
<P>
Percentage of total population who are adults*: 74.8% 
</P>
<P>
Percentage of adult population who are registered voters: 70.1% 
</P>
<P>
Percentage of registered voters who actually cast their vote: 76.6% 
</P>
<P>
Total O.C. Population: 2,257,200 
</P>
<P>
* at least 18 years old. 
</P>
<P>
Sources: California Department of Finance and O.C. registrar of voters. Mark I. 
Pinsky and Steve Emmons 
