<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COSTA MESA; 
</P>
<P>
SUMMER DAY CAMP WILL SOON RESUME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city will again offer its annual summer day camp, including daily 
activities and some overnight camp-outs, for boys and girls between the ages of 
6 and 12. The camp will run for 10 weeks, from June 25 to Aug. 31. 
</P>
<P>
Each camper must bring a sack lunch and have transportation to and from camp 
every day. 
</P>
<P>
The cost for one week of camp is $65 per child, which includes all activities, 
a beverage and an afternoon snack. Hours are from 9 a.m. to 4 p.m. The camp is 
also offering extended hours from 7 a.m. to 6 p.m. for $75 per week per child. 
</P>
<P>
Mail-in registration must be postmarked seven days before the first day of camp 
for the week selected. Mail registration to Camp Costa Mesa, P.O. Box 1200, 
Costa Mesa, Calif. 92628-1200. 
</P>
<P>
Walk-in registration is from 8 a.m. to 4 p.m. Monday through Friday at the 
Community Services Department at City Hall, 77 Fair Drive. 
</P>
<P>
For more information, call (714) 642-1569 or (714) 754-5300. 
</P>
</TEXT>
