<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: SCIENCE/TECHNOLOGY; 
</P>
<P>
HUGHES AIRCRAFT WON'T BID FOR ALL OF FORD AERONEUTRONIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Dean Takahashi, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hughes Aircraft Co. has confirmed that it is not planning to acquire a major 
defense contractor, ending speculation that the company might bid for all of 
Ford Aerospace's Aeroneutronic Division in Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Hughes spokesman Richard Doree on Monday confirmed a published statement by 
Hughes Chairman Malcom R. Currie that, given the current uncertainty of the 
defense budget, the company is not interested in buying another big defense 
operation. 
</P>
<P>
However, Currie left open the possibility that Hughes might bid on parts of the 
division if it is parceled out to bidders. Ford Motor Co. put the division up 
for sale in January. 
</P>
</TEXT>
