<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Industrial Clinics: TriCare Inc., a Santa Ana firm that provides administrative 
services to physician groups in occupational medicine, said Monday that it has 
acquired Occu-Care Inc., a chain of four industrial medical clinics, for $5.75 
million in cash and the assumption of certain liabilities. 
</P>
<P>
Larry Wasserman, TriCare's chief financial officer, said Occu-Care, based in 
Pomona, operates industrial clinics in Pomona, Riverside, Ontario and the City 
of Industry and had net revenues of $7.6 million during 1989. 
</P>
<P>
TriCare, a 5-year-old firm, generated an estimated $20 million in revenue 
during its fiscal year that ended May 31, Wasserman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
TRICARE INC; ACQUISITIONS; OCCU CARE INC; CLINICS 
</P>
