</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Tokyo area was shaken today by a moderate earthquake for the second time in 
five days. 
</P>
<P>
No injuries or damage were reported although high-speed "bullet" train services 
out of Tokyo were disrupted for several minutes. 
</P>
<P>
"These kinds of earthquakes are fairly common, and it doesn't mean we're in for 
a big one," a Meteorological Agency official said. 
</P>
<P>
The tremor had a magnitude of 5.3. Buildings in the capital swayed and windows 
rattled, but people in cars were generally unaware that a quake had occurred. 
</P>
<P>
Last week's tremor had a reading of 6.0. 
</P>
