</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
June 16 would have been Stan Laurel's 100th birthday, and the anniversary will 
be celebrated in a series of tributes in Southern California and New York City. 
</P>
<P>
Turner Network Television will broadcast a special collection of Laurel and 
Hardy films the week preceding the date. The Museum of Modern Art and the 
Museum of Moving Images in New York both plan film retrospectives. 
</P>
<P>
The United States Post Office has approved and designed a commemorative stamp 
for issue later this year or early 1991. The city of Santa Monica, where the 
comedian lived for many years, will rename a street in his honor. 
</P>
