</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MADRID 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lithuanian basketball star Arvydas Sabonis, expected to play for the Portland 
Trail Blazers in the National Basketball Assn. next season, signed a one-year 
contract extension today with Forum Filatelico of Spain. 
</P>
<P>
Team officials announced the signing but declined to say how much they would 
pay Sabonis, who helped the Soviet Union win the Olympic gold medal in 1988. 
</P>
<P>
Sabonis, a 7-foot-3 center, originally signed with the Spanish club in June, 
1989. That contract was worth $1 million, but most of the money was to go to 
sports authorities in the Soviet Union. 
</P>
<P>
Sabonis said at the time that he hoped to play in the NBA after one year in 
Spain. 
</P>
<P>
Portland, which drafted Sabonis in 1986, holds NBA rights to the 25-year-old. 
</P>
<P>
Sabonis had hoped that the less strenuous schedule in the Spanish league would 
help him to recover from an Achilles' tendon injury that had bothered him since 
before the Olympics. 
</P>
<P>
In an interview last May, Sabonis said the tendon was better. 
</P>
